    "A growing body of research investigates moral attributions toward non-LLM AI systems.",
    "Among the findings on this topic are conflicting attitudes about the moral properties of these systems.",
    "For example, people generally approve of self-driving cars making utilitarian moral decisions (e.g., killing one person to save five), but they would not want to ride in one 26.",
